3. String Functions
- concat(), concat_ws() – combine strings
- lower(), upper() – case transformations
- regexp_replace(), regexp_extract() – regex operations
- substring() – extract substrings
4. Date & Time Functions
- current_date(), current_timestamp() – get system date/time
- datediff(), months_between() – calculate differences
- date_add(), date_sub() – manipulate dates
- year(), month(), dayofweek() – extract components
5. Aggregation & Grouping
- groupBy().agg() – group and aggregate
- count(), sum(), avg(), max(), min() – basic aggregations
- collect_list(), collect_set() – gather values into arrays
6. Window Functions
- row_number(), rank(), dense_rank() – ranking
- lead(), lag() – look ahead/behind in partitions
- ntile() – bucket rows into groups
7. Null Handling
- coalesce() – first non-null value
- fillna(), dropna() – handle missing values
- isnull(), isnotnull() – check nulls
8. Array & Map Functions
- explode() – flatten arrays
- size() – length of array
- map_keys(), map_values() – extract map elements
9. Joins & Merging
- join() – inner, left, right, full joins
- union(), unionByName() – combine DataFrames
- intersect(), exceptAll() – set operations
10. File I/O Functions
- read.csv(), read.json(), read.parquet() – load data
- write.csv(), write.parquet() – save data
- option("header", True) – configure file reads/writes
11. UDFs (User Defined Functions)
- udf() – define custom Python functions for transformations
- pandas_udf() – vectorized UDFs for performance
